  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We study vacuum stability in <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math> dimensional Conformal Field Theories with external background fields. We show that the vacuum decay rate is given by a non-local two-form. This two-form is a boundary term that must be added to the effective in/out Lagrangian. The two-form is expressed in terms of a Riemann–Hilbert decomposition for background gauge fields, and its novel “functional” version in the gravitational case.</subfield>
